article.headline: Texas-Pan American 77, IPFW 61
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas (AP) -- Colin Lien scored 24 points to help lead Texas-Pan American to a 77-61 victory over IPFW on Thursday night. Lien was one of five players to score in double figures for the Broncs (11-10). Brian Burrell scored 14 points and Paul Stoll, Zach Trader and Julius Allgood each had 10. Justin Hawkins and Chris Perkins each scored 12 points for IPFW (7-14). Jakari Johnson added 10. Texas-Pan American scored 25 points off 22 IPFW turnovers. Texas-Pan American led 34-27 at the half.
